#import libraries and install packages
library(openair)
library(lubridate)
#Import data
ad_fall2012 <- read.csv2("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lourdesvera/Community_Air_Montoring/master/Wind_Analyses/Armourdale_10yrs.csv", header = TRUE, sep = ",", stringsAsFactors = FALSE )
armourdale
#rename columns
colnames(ad_fall2012) = c("Year", "Month", "Day", "Temperature", "ws", "wd")
#change some column formats
ad_fall2012$Temperature <- as.numeric(ad$Temperature)
ad_fall2012$ws <- as.numeric(ad$ws)
ad_fall2012$wd <- as.numeric(ad$wd)
#Concatenate day, month, year and convert that column into date/time format
ad_fall2012$date <- make_date(year = ad_fall2012$Year, month = ad_fall2012$Month , day = ad_fall2012$Day)
head(ad_fall2012$date)
[1] "2012-01-01" "2012-01-02" "2012-01-03" "2012-01-04" "2012-01-05" "2012-01-06"
library(weathermetrics)
#Convert Celsius to Fahrenheit
ad_fall2012$Temperature <- celsius.to.fahrenheit(ad$Temperature, round = 2)
ad_fall2012 <- selectByDate(ad_fall2012, start = "2012-09-22", end = "2012-12-20")
summary(ad_fall2012)

#prep for wind rose
ad_wr <- ad_fall2012[,c("ws", "wd")]
windRose(ad_wr)

windRose(ad_wr, ws = "ws", wd = "wd",breaks=c(0, 2, 5,8, 11, 17), auto.text=FALSE, paddle=FALSE, annotate=FALSE, grid.line=5, key = list(labels = c(">0-2", ">2-5", ">5-8", ">8-11", ">11-17")), key.footer = "Fall 2012 Wind Speed Plot in Armourdale, KS (m/s)", key.position = "bottom",par.settings=list(axis.line=list(col="lightgray")), col = c("#4f4f4f", "#0a7cb9", "#f9be00", "#ff7f2f", "#d7153a"))
